# {{project_slug}} Helm Chart

This Helm chart deploys the {{project_slug}} pebble service to a Kubernetes cluster.

## Prerequisites

- Kubernetes 1.16+
- Helm 3.0+

## Installing the Chart

```bash
helm install {{project_slug}} ./helm/{{project_slug}}
```

## Uninstalling the Chart

```bash
helm uninstall {{project_slug}}
```

## Configuration

The following table lists the configurable parameters of the {{project_slug}} chart and their default values.

| Parameter | Description | Default |
| --------- | ----------- | ------- |
| `replicaCount` | Number of replicas | `1` |
| `image.repository` | Image repository | `{{project_slug}}` |
| `image.tag` | Image tag | `latest` |
| `image.pullPolicy` | Image pull policy | `IfNotPresent` |
| `service.type` | Service type | `ClusterIP` |
| `service.port` | Service port | `80` |
| `service.targetPort` | Container port | `8000` |
| `resources.limits.cpu` | CPU limits | `500m` |
| `resources.limits.memory` | Memory limits | `512Mi` |
| `resources.requests.cpu` | CPU requests | `100m` |
| `resources.requests.memory` | Memory requests | `128Mi` |
| `environment` | Environment variables | `PORT: 8000` |
